&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and strategize across formats: LinkedIn posts, youtube scripts, Twitter threads, product narratives, event recaps, and more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex ideas from product, sales, and leadership into content that resonates with senior enterprise buyers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring structure to the content calendar: define pillars, build reuse into the workflow, and think beyond the next post.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Script video content for the studio, understanding that what reads well on paper lands differently on camera.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be present where the story is: events, offsites, customer conversations. You treat those as source material, not scheduling conflicts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside AI tools to accelerate first drafts, then apply the judgment and editorial layer that makes the output worth publishing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–5 years of content writing experience in a B2B SaaS, tech, or developer-tools environment, with a portfolio that shows range across formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong instinct for audience segmentation and you write differently for a CHRO than for an engineering leader, and it shows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to hold strategy and execution simultaneously: you can take a content brief and run with it, without four rounds of alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;re AI-native in practice&lt;/strong&gt;, not just in theory. You use tools like Claude Code, ChatGPT, or similar as a starting point, and then you make it better.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re based in Bangalore and comfortable working in-person at the studio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at building content systems, not just one-off pieces you think about pillar topics, reuse, and narrative arcs across a calendar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
